        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 14 at 11:22PM EDT by NWS Charleston WV</headline>
        <description>At 1122 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Craftsville, or near Whitesburg, moving east at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Trammel, Nora, Clinchco, Clintwood, Davenport, McClure, and Haysi.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
